  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the Ministry of Migration and Asylum of Greece in Providing Holistic Health Care Response in Islands&apos; Reception and Accommodation Centers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the framework of the Project, IOM will support the set-up and operationalization of biochemistry laboratories and radiology units in the Reception and Identification Centers (RIC) of Lesvos, Chios, Samos, Leros and Kos. Through the proposed activities, namely the set-up of the said medical facilities and the deployment of licensed health professionals (senior laboratory technicians and radiologists) IOM seeks to relieve the burden of the national health care system and reinforce the Greek National Organization of Public Health (EODY) that does not have sufficient capacity to serve the RICs&apos; medical caseload due to limited resources, coupled with COVID-19 restrictions and limitations. Ultimately, the project will contribute to strengthening the capacity of EODY in carrying out entry and periodic health screening and medical examinations within the scope of primary health care, thus enhancing the health and well-being of migrants residing in RICs.</narrative>
  </description>
